Full Description: Adium is a free instant messaging application for Mac OS X  that can connect to [AIM]( http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/aim-2), MSN , [Jabber]( http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/jabber), [Yahoo]( http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/yahoo), IRC, [Twitter]( http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/twitter), and more. It is written using Mac OS X's Cocoa API and released under the GNU GPL. As it is based on the libpurple protocol library, Adium has the ability to connect its users to any number of messaging accounts on any combination of supported messaging services, and then it allows them to chat with other people using those services. Adium doesn’t host any Instant Messaging services by itself because Adium is a third party client, which connects its clients to services run by other people. Adium was launched in 2000, and it is developed by the Adium team.

Description: SparkX is a B2B Fintech company, first of its kind to scalably verify & help recover unpaid royalties for licensed trademarks and patents.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: SparkX is a B2B FinTech solution that uses AI and Blockchain technology to solve the $100B royalty leakage in the licensing industry. We collect supply chain data for each product SKU every time a royalty report is submitted to the licensor. By comparing the licensee-provided sales data with our data we can immediately identify issues and allow licensee and licensor to agree on the accurate royalty amount.  Our solution builds increased confidence in the accuracy of each royalty report, which reduces later need for audits.  Further, our solution works in tandem with a licensee's or licensor's royalty management systems, without requiring a technical integration, minimizing disruption to existing business processes. SparkX is currently assembling a top team of specialists in the areas of licensing and software engineering, dedicated to creating a new and better solution to the problems of licensing. Currently we have a few angel investors, and we are seeking additional funding.
Industry Groups: Administrative Services, Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Financial Services, Information Technology, Science and Engineering, Software

Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Indiana Women’s Prison is a correctional facility of Indiana Department of Correction in United States. Established in 1873, it served as the first adult female correctional facility in the country. The Indiana Women’s Prison was not only the United States’ first separate institution for female prisoners, but was also the first maximum-security female correctional facility in the nation.  As of 2005 it had an average daily population of 420 inmates, most of whom are members of special-needs populations, such as geriatric, mentally ill, pregnant, and juveniles sentenced as adults. By the end of 2015 the population increased to 599 inmates. Security levels range from medium to maximum.The prison holds Indiana’s only death row for women; however, it currently has no death row inmates.

Mobil emerged from the breakup of Standard Oil, which occurred in 1911. Standard Oil was dissolved by the Sherman Antitrust Act, and one of the 33 companies that resulted from the split was Standard Oil of New York, which eventually became Mobil. In 1955, Standard Oil of New York renamed itself as Socony Mobil Oil Company, and in 1963 it adopted the name Mobil. The signature had finally brand emerged. In 1998, [Exxon](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/exxon) and Mobil signed a $73.3 billion agreement that would merge the two companies together, and become **[ExxonMobil](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/exxonmobil)**.  Today, Mobil still acts as the signature brand for **[ExxonMobil](http://www.crunchbase.com/organization/exxonmobil)**, and is a well recognized gas station around the world.

Description: Scottish Kilt™, USA is an online custom made kilt company, shop full range of Scottish, Irish Kilts & Accessories are available to order.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The Scottish Kilt has a rich history dating back to the 16th century when it was originally worn for practical purposes by soldiers. Made from thick wool, the long length and open body of the kilt provided warmth and freedom of movement. Every kilt was handmade with care and pride, as there were no kilt factories at that time. As the kilt became more popular, it became a symbol of Scottish heritage and culture and was worn by people from all walks of life. However, the traditional art of making kilts has been lost over time, as manufactured kilts have taken over. These generic styles lack the richness and quality of the original kilts and are made with cheap materials that do not do justice to the Scottish culture. At Scottish Kilt Shop, we refuse to compromise on the authenticity of the Scottish kilt. We believe that every Scot should take pride in their culture by wearing premium kilts that reflect their history and heritage. We use high-quality materials to create each kilt by hand, in the original process, so that you can be proud to own a piece of true Scottish heritage. We offer a wide range of kilts for sale, including mens kilts, so that everyone can experience the beauty and tradition of the Scottish kilt.

Description: BSE is a far cry from its apartment living room beginnings in 1979 where Bill Silva began his career promoting local concerts.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Bill Silva Entertainment (BSE) is a far cry from its apartment living room beginnings in 1979 where Bill Silva began his career promoting local concerts. Today, the fully-staffed organization includes Bill Silva Presents (BSP), a major concerts promotion and touring division; Bill Silva Management (BSM), an artist management division; Silva Music Publishing (SMP), a music publishing and licensing division; a 20-year relationship with the Hollywood Bowl to present concerts there; and Bill Silva Ventures, which invests in early stage startups and as an LP in venture capital funds. Since 1979, Bill Silva Entertainment has produced over 10,000 events from small clubs to major stadiums all over the world. Shows produced have included such prodigious talents as Simon & Garfunkel, Santana, The Police, Madonna, Nirvana, Eric Clapton and Bob Dylan. Bill Silva founded Bill Silva Presents in 1979 while at school at the University of California, San Diego. BSP was so successful in San Diego that Bill then expanded his concert operations throughout the Southwest United States to Phoenix, Las Vegas, Texas, Idaho and Los Angeles. When BSE moved to Los Angeles in 1999, Bill had become one of the top impresarios in North America, working with artists such as The Who, Devo, Pat Benatar, INXS, Diana Ross and Willie Nelson. Universal Studios’ concert division bought BSE in 1999, which was later purchased by House of Blues Concerts. Bill Silva left that venture in 2003 and re-formed Bill Silva Presents as his own entrepreneurial company.
Industry Groups: Events, Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio, Sales and Marketing

Our goal is to build a complete line of HMO products to address various gut-related health problems, with different product forms and flavors.
